body:
### Version

Yosys 0.38+0 (git sha1 46838172c, clang++ 11.1.0 -fPIC -Os)

### On which OS did this happen?

macOS

### Reproduction Steps

Read the below into Yosys with the Verific frontend.

 ```
module top(clk, write_enable_a, read_enable_a, read_data_a,
           addr_a, write_data_a,
           write_enable_b, addr_b, write_data_b);

localparam DATA_WIDTH = 16;
localparam ADDR_WIDTH = 16;
input wire clk;
input wire write_enable_a;
input wire write_enable_b;
input wire read_enable_a;

input wire [ADDR_WIDTH - 1 : 0] addr_a;
input wire [ADDR_WIDTH - 1 : 0] addr_b;
output reg [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] read_data_a;
input wire [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] write_data_a;
input wire [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] write_data_b;

reg [DATA_WIDTH - 1 : 0] mem [2**ADDR_WIDTH - 1 : 0];

always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (write_enable_a)
        mem[addr_a] <= write_data_a;
    if (write_enable_b)
        mem[addr_b] <= write_data_b;
    if (read_enable_a)
        read_data_a <= mem[addr_a];
end

endmodule
```

### Expected Behavior

The memory writes are represented faithfully, with the second taking precedence over the first in case of conflict.

### Actual Behavior

Two `$memwr` cells get emitted with the same value for the `PRIORITY` parameter, so the priority relationship between the two ports is lost. No soft logic is emitted to establish the relationship either.
```
  cell $memwr $verific$clk_write_port_8$memtest.sv:24$15
    parameter \WIDTH 16
    parameter \ABITS 16
    parameter \PRIORITY 0
    parameter \CLK_POLARITY 1
    parameter \CLK_ENABLE 1
    parameter \MEMID "\\mem"
    connect \DATA $verific$n24$5
    connect \ADDR \addr_b
    connect \CLK \clk
    connect \EN ...
  end

  attribute \src "memtest.sv:22.9-22.20"
  cell $memwr $verific$clk_write_port_5$memtest.sv:22$13
    parameter \WIDTH 16
    parameter \ABITS 16
    parameter \PRIORITY 0
    parameter \CLK_POLARITY 1
    parameter \CLK_ENABLE 1
    parameter \MEMID "\\mem"
    connect \DATA $verific$n5$4
    connect \ADDR \addr_a
    connect \CLK \clk
    connect \EN ...
  end
```

